@baentsch 

ML-DSA update has changed the size of _Extension - Supported Groups_ from "00 12" to "00 14" because by default we enabled x25519_mlkem512 (and this gives the extra 2 bytes).

ML-DSA update has changed the size of _Extension - Signature Algorithms_ from "00 36" to "00 3c" because we added three signature algoithms (6 bytes).

Together, 8 bytes are added; thus, the clienthello size has increased from 10018 to 10026.

In short, the clienthello includes more KEX/SIG options; however, when we run the test, it still picks SSL_GROUP_X25519_FRODO640AES.

@bhess The HQC in oqs-provider 0.5.2 & 0.5.3 is the old one, so the test server does not need any updates now until the new versions of liboqs and oqs-provider are released.

